Package it.polimi.ingsw.socket

Interface SocketManager<IN extends Packet,ACK_IN extends AckPacket,ACK_OUT extends AckPacket,OUT extends Packet>

Type Parameters:
IN - type of Packet that can be received
ACK_IN - type of AckPacket that can be received
ACK_OUT - type of AckPacket that can be sent
OUT - type of Packet that can be sent
All Superinterfaces:
AutoCloseable, Closeable
All Known Subinterfaces:
ClientSocketManager, ServerSocketManager
All Known Implementing Classes:
ClientSocketManagerImpl, ServerSocketManagerImpl, SocketManagerImpl
public interface SocketManager<IN extends Packet,ACK_IN extends AckPacket,ACK_OUT extends AckPacket,OUT extends Packet> extends Closeable
Handle socket communication from multiple threads, using a queue. Allows sending acks and replies.

  • Method Details

    • send

      void send(OUT p) throws IOException
      Send a packet and wait for an ack. The given packet is wrapped in a SimpleSeqPacket and the SimpleSeqPacket.seqN() is set. The packet is added to a queue to be sent. Wait for a SimpleAckPacket with SeqAckPacket.seqAck() == SimpleSeqPacket.seqN()
      Parameters:
      p - packet to be sent
      Throws:
      IOException - if sending and/or receiving fails
      InterruptedIOException - if interrupted while sending and/or receiving

    • send

      <R extends ACK_IN> SocketManager.PacketReplyContext<ACK_IN,ACK_OUT,R> send(OUT p, Class<R> replyType) throws IOException
      Send a packet and wait for an ack. The given packet is wrapped in a SimpleSeqPacket and the SimpleSeqPacket.seqN() is set. The packet is added to a queue to be sent. Wait for an AckPacket of the given type and with SeqAckPacket.seqAck() == SimpleSeqPacket.seqN()
      Parameters:
      p - packet to be sent
      replyType - type of the AckPacket to wait for
      Returns:
      SocketManager.PacketReplyContext the context of the received ack
      Throws:
      IOException - if sending fails
      InterruptedIOException - if interrupted while receiving

    • setOnClose

      void setOnClose(@Nullable @Nullable SocketManager.OnCloseHook onClose)
      Hook which allows doing cleanup before and after the SocketManager is closed
      Parameters:
      onClose - hook which will be called on socket close. The actual SocketManager close method will be passed as a parameter and the hook itself will be in charge of calling it at what it deems to be the right time.
